						<summary>

						<p>Damaged. This inscription refers to the gift of 10 poṉ for renovation and repair works undertaken in the portion of the south wall of the temple by Sakkaraśar, son of Āyilu-araśar. Tirupputkuḻipiriyaṉ was the accountant of the temple.</p>						

